The paper deals with the problem of estimating a rank-one matrix in Gaussian noise under a probabilistic model for the left and right factors of the matrix. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SI), data structures (cs.DS), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). However, given the focus on probabilistic models and iterative estimation procedures, cs.IT and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories.
